name: Harper College (The L Building)
directions: The restrooms can be located in the hallway between the L building and the P building. There are two gender-neutral restrooms (in this location on campus). One is on the first floor and one is on the second floor of the L building (the second floor is the same level as the library and the bookstore, but in another hallway and around the corner). There are three floors in the L building (and two in the P building). On the first floor of the L building, the restroom is next to a women's multi-user restroom and on the second floor of the L building, the restroom is next to the men's multi-user restroom. They are in the same spot on each floor. There are elevators nearby.
comment: You can check the building hours on Harper College's website and be sure to join Harper Pride Club!

comment: Hours vary but generally open from 11 or noon to 10pm.  Plenty of fun social activities at night, great place to go out with friends and not worry.  Restrooms are in pretty plain view of the door, although one is further back a hall.  Snacks and sodas available if beer isn't your thing.  Plenty of beer options for a night out and very causal atmosphere overall

name: Knight Library
directions:
Enter the building through the set of doors on the right side, then turn right, and then keep an eye out to your left. The bathroom will be down a short hall.
If you need to take the accessible entrance (the left set of doors), turn right and go all the way through the main lobby, and past the second set of stairs. Then the bathroom will be around a corner to your left.
